<br>
These poll results represent a spectrum between <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">casual</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mages, who would like to solo post-60 about as well as they did pre-60, say about one AA per five hours, and <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">covetous</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mages, who would like to solo about as well as kiters and charmers, say about one AA per hour.<br>
<br>
I intend to focus on the casual end of the spectrum first, as represented by the proposal <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Un-nerf non-PoP experience.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
My gut feeling is that in order to satisfy the covetous end of the spectrum, mages would require a big boost in power, which I suspect is not justifiable.<br>
